        }
    }
```

I created a small "editable field" where if you click on the text, it'll change to a text box which you can then modify.
However, I'm seeing some really strange behavior from hitting "Escape": If I click on the text, and edit the text, and hit "Enter" everything's fine. If I hit "Escape" it appears to delete the last element.
So if I click on the Text, type something and hit "Escape" it deletes div "savedValue". If I do it again, it deletes span "textField".
My intention was obviously to change "Text" back to "_savedValue" if they hit escape. And it seems like it might work, but it keeps deleting the elements.
Any other warnings, caveats, or better ways to do what I'm trying to do appreciated.
Thanks
```
<div>
    @if (_editing)
    {
        <input id="textField" bind="Text" onkeyup="@OnKeyUp" />
    } 
    else
    {
        <span id="textField" onclick="@OnTextClicked">@Text</span>
    }
    <div id="savedValue">@_savedValue</div>
</div>
@functions{
    [Parameter]
    string Text { get; set; }

    [Parameter]
    private Action<string> TextChanged { get; set; }

    bool _editing = false;

    string _savedValue;

    void OnTextClicked()
    {
        _editing = true;
        _savedValue = Text;
    }

    void OnKeyUp(UIKeyboardEventArgs eventArgs)
    {
        if (eventArgs.Key == "Enter" || eventArgs.Key == "Escape") //This causes the issue
        {
            _editing = false;
        }
    }
}
```

You can check [repo](https://github.com/Lupusa87/Issue1254) with is created for this issue
Also 1 min [video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3O3yhAPcCrM) demonstration.

My component has parameter k, based on this k value I generate component body overriding BuildRenderTree method.

For example:
if k = 2 result will be:
```
<p>1</p>
<p>2</p>
```

if k = 3 result will be:
```
<p>1</p>
<p>2</p>
<p>3</p>
```


If I change k parameter with is binded to parent page variable, I can't get updated UI because BuildRenderTree method not fires.
I have slider to change k,  new Parameter is receiving on setparameters method but rendering not gets invoked.


 ```
    <div>
        <component1 bind-k="@CurrValue" />
        <input type="range" min="1" max="100"  bind="@CurrValue"/>
    </div>

@functions
{
    int CurrValue = 75;
}

```


```
 public class component1  : BlazorComponent
    {
     
        [Parameter]
        public int k { get; set; }

        [Parameter]
        public Action<int> kChanged { get; set; }

        protected override void BuildRenderTree(RenderTreeBuilder builder)
        {
            int s = 0;
            for (int i = 1; i <= k; i++)
            {
              builder.OpenElement(s++,"p");
              builder.AddContent(s++,i.ToString());
              builder.CloseElement();
            }
        }

        public override void SetParameters(ParameterCollection parameters)
        {
           // this prints new value on every change, so binding is working and new value is receiving
            Console.WriteLine(parameters.GetValueOrDefault<int>("k"))
            base.SetParameters(parameters);
        }
  }
```

**If I use renderfragment I can do it, I force rendering because I can access builder inside oninit method**
```

@DynamicFragment

@functions {

[Parameter]
public int k { get; set; }

RenderFragment DynamicFragment { get; set; }


protected override void OnInit()
{
   DynamicFragment = builder =>
    {
            int s = 0;
            for (int i = 1; i <= k; i++)
            {
              builder.OpenElement(s++,"p");
              builder.AddContent(s++,i.ToString());
              builder.CloseElement();
            }
    }
}
}
```

It is not convenient to use renderfragment everywhere and it is not solution, component should be get updated when parameter is changed.

**So problem is that I can't access RenderTreeBuilder builder in my case (from setparameter method).**

**Finally I need somehow to invoke RenderTreeBuilder method after parameter change to update UI.**
